It honestly doesn’t sound like long, delta was a horrid base. Utopia was made by RandQm, which all he really did was clean it up and re-package it so it didn’t have a 1mb Client class and it actually worked properly.

Your first click looks fine (compared it to my PI, did the conversion)
c.objectX = c.getInStream().readSignedWordBigEndianA();
c.objectId = c.getInStream().readUnsignedWord();
c.objectY = c.getInStream().readUnsignedWordA();
That’s PI’s…
Remove the c. and change getInStream to inStream:
objectX = inStream().readSignedWordBigEndianA();
objectId = inStream().readUnsignedWord();
objectY = inStream().readUnsignedWordA();
Then you just name them how it is in delta and it’s the same…
